<p>Umber huffed, Sage croaked, and Ben was still fascinated with the multitude of blinking lights on the console. He knew that he was not going to figure out how to work this contraption without blowing himself up or the second child. Neither would be desireable. He knew this was a second chance and he did not need to blow. Scrambling up near the console to get a better look, Umber started to form his questions for Virgil.</p>
